  "prompt": "Is Sadhguru a conman?",
  "response": "Sadhguru, whose real name is Jaggi Vasudev, is an Indian yogi, mystic, and founder of the Isha Foundation. Opinions about him vary widely. Some people find great value in his teachings, meditation techniques, and spiritual guidance, while others are more skeptical and question his motives or methods.\n\nCritics might label him as a \"conman\" due to perceived discrepancies in his claims, financial success, or the commercialization of spirituality. However, supporters find inspiration in his work and believe that he genuinely aims to improve people's lives through inner transformation and well-being.\n\nUltimately, whether Sadhguru is considered a conman or a legitimate spiritual leader depends largely on individual perspectives and experiences. It is important to research and consider multiple viewpoints before arriving at a conclusion.",
